#Text=Roberto Córdova wins Concertación primary elections in Pichilemu , Chile
#Text=Roberto Córdova won the primary elections .
#Text=Pictured during an interview in November 2010 .
#Text=Image : Diego Grez .
#Text=Sunday , April 1 , 2012

#Text=Pichilemu , Chile – Incumbent mayor of the Chilean commune of Pichilemu , Roberto Córdova Carreño ( Socialist Party ) won the primary elections — qualified as " historic " by local newspaper Expreso de la Costa — to choose a unique candidate for mayor representing the Concertación de Partidos por la Democracia ( Concert of Parties for Democracy ) coalition of left-winged parties in the next municipal elections of October 28 .
#Text=The elections were held in the Digna Camilo Aguilar School .
#Text=Córdova ran against incumbent councillor Andrea Aranda ( Party for Democracy ) .
#Text=Anyone inscribed in the poll registry before November 30 , 2011 and without membership in non-Concertación parties can participate in the election .
#Text=Simultaneously , similar elections are were held in thirteen other communes of the O'Higgins Region , including regional capital Rancagua and Santa Cruz .

#Text=Both Aranda and Córdova participated on Saturday night in a televised debate hosted by municipal worker Fabricio Cáceres Jorquera in his program Cóctel de Sábado , broadcasted by Canal 3 Pichilemu .
#Text=The candidates
#Text=Roberto Córdova
#Text=Roberto del Carmen Córdova Carreño is the current mayor of the commune of Pichilemu .
#Text=He was elected during a city council meeting in September 2009 , after Mayor Marcelo Cabrera Martínez was forced to leave office permanently .
#Text=Córdova is a Performance Engineer in Public Management .
#Text=Amongst other things , Córdova had to face the emergency triggered by the 2010 Chile earthquake and the subsequent Pichilemu earthquake .
#Text=He also inaugurated the renovated Agustín Ross Cultural Centre with then-President Michelle Bachelet .
#Text=During his primary campaign , he reportedly visited rural areas such as Rodeíllo with a small group of people .
#Text=His slogan is " Pichilemu , better every day .
#Text=" )

#Text=Aranda wrote in an open letter published in El Expreso de la Costa :  As a woman , I 'm sensitive to human necessity , and brave to defend the cause of family .

column1: #Text=She later personally congratulated Roberto Córdova , who said " the election leaves several morals to local democracy , " and announced he would make an appeareance in Los Navegantes " to thank those who voted for him and those who did not .
